e of democracy, the universality of democratic ideals, and the practice of cross-cultural research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyvCross-cultural studies. 0aDemocracyxCross-cultural studies. 0aDemocracyzSenegal. 4aAfrican Hist & Diaspora. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171839740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501718397423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501718397/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles